      "content": "Wait, so are you saying that almost any type of regulation is inherently bad? even if it's just something minor like age verification or preventing illegal content? i'm trying to see if there's any legitimate middle ground or if, philosophically speaking, there's no such thing as \"safe\" regulation in this context.",
